events.name: Skid Row And Great White
events.info: This event is General Admission, standing room only. Head to the Outdoor Plaza at Harrah's Reno on Sunday, June 30th for Skid Row with special guests Great White! It's sure to be a night full of great rock 'n' roll! Since their start in 1986, Skid Row have released numerous classic tracks, including "Youth Gone Wild," "I Remember You," "18 and Life," "We Are The Damned," "Monkey Business" and "Let's Go." Special guests Great White have been at it since 1977 and are responsible for "Once Bitten Twice Shy," "Rock me," "House of Broken Love," "Lady Red Light" and other hits!

events.info: Rodrigo y Gabriela are bringing their Mettavolution Tour to the Outdoor Plaza at Harrah's Reno on Friday, July 26th! The duo's impending album, Mettavolution, is not only their first release in five years, but it's also the act's most ambitious effort in their twenty-year career together! Don't miss out on experiencing one of the top live acts in the world.

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Day of Onsale: 10am - 12noon. Otherwise the box office opens at 10 am on the day of a performance.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, MC, AMX
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call is available two (2) hours prior to show time. Will Call can be picked up at the Events Center South Ticket Office on the corner of Center St. and Fourth St. Customers MUST present the actual credit card used for the purchase, a valid photo ID and the Ticketmaster confirmation number in order to receive their tickets

venues.parkingDetail: There are a limited number of parking spaces available in the National Bowling Stadium parking lot. There are also many public and private lots situated near the Events Center. Customers can park at Circus Circus or Fitzgerald's. Sorry >>NO<< RV parking available in the National Bowling Stadium parking lot.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating is located on platforms at the bottom of all 100 section seating. Accessible doors to facility are located at the Southwest, Southeast and Northwest entrances

generalInfo.generalRule: NO Audio NO Video NO Smoking anywhere inside the Reno Events Center. There is a designated smoking area provided outside Portal A.
generalInfo.childRule: All Ages are welcome. For most events no ticket is required for ages 0-23months, as long as the child does not occupy a seat of their own. For events such as "Sesame Street", "Barney", or "Dragon Tales", a ticket is required for anyone 12 months or older.
